[[[break]]]added at line 0: *lime {code or: Why Clark Glymour Might Be a Bayesian After All

Glymour's 1984? paper "Why I Am Not a Bayesian" has been influential in setting the agenda for attacking and defending Bayesianism.

Using Glymour's own points, I show that he (or anyone who holds the position he held in 1984) need not fear Bayesianism, if by "Bayesianism" we understand the most sophisticated version of this position currently available.
}*